181
00:09:53,966 --> 00:09:57,600
So if I got a microservice
with just a few, maybe a thousand,

182
00:09:57,766 --> 00:10:01,066
requests, a minute

183
00:10:01,866 --> 00:10:04,933
or less, then this is a really good, easy
way to go.

184
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:09,833
It decreases the complexity
and also makes it so I can easily move,

185
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:13,333
in and out of my,

186
00:10:13,666 --> 00:10:18,766
microservice architectures
where I always making that decision on

187
00:10:18,766 --> 00:10:22,766
do I create a new microservice to do that,
or do I keep it in the same code?

188
00:10:23,033 --> 00:10:25,066
So that helps out a
lot with that sort of thing.
